;}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"how to create a sitemap in wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"sitemap generator wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"wordpress sitemap\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"wordpress sitemap plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"wordpress xml sitemap\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=22654\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:357:\"<p>Are you wondering how to create a sitemap in WordPress? In this post, we’ll explain what an sitemap is and how to create a sitemap in WordPress the easy way.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">How to Create a Sitemap in WordPress (The Easy Way)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18400:\"<p>Are you wondering what a sitemap is and how to create a sitemap in WordPress?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A sitemap helps search engines easily navigate through your website content. It gives them a list of all your content in a machine-readable format.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this post, we’ll explain what a sitemap is and how to create a sitemap in WordPress the easy way.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here’s a quick overview of what we’ll cover in this post. Simply click on these quick links to jump straight to different sections.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"#what-is-a-sitemap\">What Is a Sitemap?</a></li><li><a href=\"#why-you-should-create-a-sitemap\">Why You Should Create a Sitemap</a></li><li><a href=\"#does-wordpress-automatically-generate-a-sitemap\">Does WordPress Automatically Generate a Sitemap?</a></li><li><a href=\"#create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way\">Create a Sitemap in WordPress The Easy Way</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-a-sitemap\"><strong>What Is a Sitemap?</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A sitemap is a file or a special webpage that lists all your website content in an XML format, so that search engines like Google can discover and index your site’s content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sitemaps used to be in HTML format, and could be viewed as a list of all pages included on a website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nowadays, the usage of sitemaps has evolved and they are published in an XML format instead of HTML with search engines as their target audience. Not people like in the past.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simply put, a sitemap is a way for website owners to tell search engines about all existing pages on their website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It also tells search engines which links on your website are more important than others, and how frequently you update your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While sitemaps won’t directly boost your search engine rankings, they allow search engines to better crawl your website. This means that they can find more content and start showing it in search results, which can result in higher rankings and more traffic to your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Without an XML Sitemap, it would take longer for your content to appear on or be removed from search engines.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"why-you-should-create-a-sitemap\"><strong>Why You Should Create a Sitemap</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"382\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-xml-sitemap.png\" alt=\"WordPress XML Sitemap\" class=\"wp-image-22694\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-xml-sitemap.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-xml-sitemap-300x162.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-xml-sitemap-704x382.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/wordpress-xml-sitemap-600x325.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like mentioned, sitemaps are used to ensure that search engines can easily crawl your website.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sitemaps are important from a search engine optimization (SEO) perspective. If you want to learn more about SEO, please check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, simply adding a sitemap doesn&#8217;t affect search rankings. But if there’s a page on your site that’s not indexed, then a sitemap provides a way to let search engines know about that page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Make It Easier for Search Engines to Discover Your Content</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Sitemaps are also extremely useful when you <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/start-a-wordpress-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">first start a blog</a> or <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">create a new website</a> because most new websites don’t have any <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/glossary/backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">backlinks</a>. The lack of backlinks makes it harder for search engines to discover all new content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, search engines like Google and Bing allow new website owners to submit a sitemap in their webmaster tools, so that  search engine bots can discover and index recently published content on their sites.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sitemaps are equally important for established and popular websites. They allow you to highlight which pages are the most important, more frequently updated, and so forth. In this way, search engines can visit and index your content accordingly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that you know why you need a sitemap, you might be wondering how to create one. But first, let&#8217;s explain what the automatically generated WordPress sitemap includes and why it&#8217;s a good idea to <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/\">create your own sitemap</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"does-wordpress-automatically-generate-a-sitemap\"><strong>Does WordPress Automatically Generate a Sitemap?</strong></h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, WordPress includes a basic sitemap without the use of a plugin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This automatically generated sitemap includes your posts, post types, categories, tags, and archive pages.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, it also includes anything you might have no-indexed, which can cause errors on your site. There’s no way to customize the default WordPress sitemap without knowing PHP code.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you feel that coding isn’t for you, we have the perfect solution! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But if that still didn&#8217;t convince you, please check out our post about whether you should<a href=\"https://aioseo.com/wordpress-xml-sitemaps-vs-all-in-one-seo-sitemaps/\"> use a WordPress sitemap or create your own</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress-the-easy-way\"><strong>Create a Sitemap in WordPress&nbsp;</strong>The Easy Way</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"458\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/all-in-one-seo-homepage.png\" alt=\"Create a sitemap in WordPress using AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22702\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/all-in-one-seo-homepage.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/all-in-one-seo-homepage-300x188.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/all-in-one-seo-homepage-600x376.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There&#8217;s an easy way to create a sitemap in WordPress using the most powerful and user-friendly WordPress SEO plugin in the market: <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO).</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>With AIOSEO, you can make sure that Google knows which pages are the most important on your site, and only ranks your high-quality content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The XML sitemaps are easy to use and you can customize them, so that you can optimize your site for higher rankings and maximum traffic.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You get to choose to include or exclude:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Images and galleries</li><li>Password-protected posts</li><li>Custom post types</li><li>Media attachment pages</li><li>Archive pages for tags, categories, authors</li><li>and more</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Better yet, AIOSEO will also automatically notify search engines whenever you publish, update, or delete content on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You also have the option to include <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/features/video-seo-sitemaps/\">video sitemaps</a> and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">Google News sitemaps.</a> For more details, please visit our post on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/submit-your-site-to-google-news/\">how to submit your WordPress site to Google News.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s show you how to create a sitemap in WordPress the easy way. The sitemap is enabled by default, so you, basically, only need to install <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/docs/installing-all-in-one-seo-pro/\">AIOSEO</a> and it&#8217;s set!</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Customizing Your Sitemap </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>But if you&#8217;re a more advanced user, we&#8217;ll show you how to customize your sitemap in a few easy steps.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To get started, go to <strong>Sitemaps</strong> in the <strong>All in One SEO</strong> menu.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"430\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"How to create an sitemap in WordPress the easy way using AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22655\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-300x177.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemaps-menu-item-in-all-in-one-seo-600x353.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, click on <strong>General Sitemap </strong>in the top main navigation menu. &nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This will open the General Sitemap window, where you can see that <strong>Enable Sitemap</strong> is set to on.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"General sitemap settings - enable sitemap in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22656\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/enable-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you can go ahead and click on the <strong>Open Sitemap</strong> button to view your XML sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"General sitemap settings - open sitemap in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22657\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x142.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/open-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x284.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve opened the sitemap, you&#8217;ll see an index page for your XML sitemap that looks like this:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"404\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Create an XML sitemap in AIOSEO - example of index page  \" class=\"wp-image-22658\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x166.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x332.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The index page lists all the sitemaps for your site, and each sitemap contains a different type of content.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, you can see there are different sitemaps for posts, pages, attachments, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"404\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-post-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Create an XML sitemap in AIOSEO - example of sitemaps for posts, pages, attachments, etc.\" class=\"wp-image-22659\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-post-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-post-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x166.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/example-xml-post-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x332.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Click on each WordPress sitemap URL in the index overview to view a list of that specific content.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>Configuring Your XML Sitemap</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, that you know how to view your XML Sitemap, let’s move on to the basic <strong>Sitemap Settings.</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s start by deciding whether you want to have an index page for your sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have a small website (less than a few hundred URLs), you don’t really need an index page, and you can set the <strong>Enable Sitemap Indexes</strong> button to <strong>Disabled</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"721\" height=\"173\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemap-settings-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-22662\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemap-settings-in-all-in-one-seo.png 721w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemap-settings-in-all-in-one-seo-300x72.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/sitemap-settings-in-all-in-one-seo-600x144.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 721px) 100vw, 721px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re in doubt, just leave it in the <strong>Enabled </strong>mode.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, you can change the <strong>Links Per Sitemap</strong> setting if you need to, but most users should leave it as-is. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"721\" height=\"103\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/links-per-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png\" alt=\"Sitemap indexes enabled - links per sitemap in AIOSEO\" class=\"wp-image-22663\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/links-per-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo.png 721w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/links-per-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-300x43.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/links-per-sitemap-in-all-in-one-seo-600x86.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 721px) 100vw, 721px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After that, you need to decide what content you want to include in your sitemap. There are 2 settings to consider, <strong>Post Types</strong> and <strong>Taxonomies</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"236\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-all-in-one-seo-1.png\" alt=\"Sitemap post types and taxonomies settings - include all post types and taxonomies\" class=\"wp-image-22806\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-all-in-one-seo-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-all-in-one-seo-1-300x97.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-all-in-one-seo-1-600x194.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to include all content, you can leave the <strong>Include All Post Types</strong> and <strong>Include All Taxonomies</strong> check boxes checked.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On the other hand, if you uncheck these boxes, you’ll see a list of all your content post types and taxonomies and can select which ones to include in your sitemap.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"372\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-options-for-xml-sitemap-1.png\" alt=\"XML sitemap settings in AIOSEO - a list of all your content post types and taxonomies\" class=\"wp-image-22807\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-options-for-xml-sitemap-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-options-for-xml-sitemap-1-300x153.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/post-types-and-taxonomies-options-for-xml-sitemap-1-600x306.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Any content that has been set to be excluded from search results or set to no index in Sitemap Settings won’t appear in this list.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, you have the option to decide whether to include <strong>Date Archives</strong> and <strong>Author Archives</strong> in your sitemap. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"730\" height=\"272\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/date-archive-and-author-sitemaps-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png\" alt=\"XML sitemap settings in AIOSEO - date archives and author archives\" class=\"wp-image-22808\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/date-archive-and-author-sitemaps-in-all-in-one-seo-1.png 730w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/date-archive-and-author-sitemaps-in-all-in-one-seo-1-300x112.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/date-archive-and-author-sitemaps-in-all-in-one-seo-1-600x224.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 730px) 100vw, 730px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Date and Author Archives are automatically created by WordPress when you publish news posts on your site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend that you don’t include these in the sitemap and leave them in the <strong>Disabled </strong>mode since they have little value in search results. But if you still want to include these, you simply click on the <strong>Enabled</strong> button so it turns blue.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As simple as that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope this article helped answer all your questions about WordPress XML sitemaps and how to easily create a sitemap for your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also want to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-do-an-seo-competitor-analysis/\">how to do an SEO competitor analysis</a> so that you can find out where you stand in relation to your competitors and what keywords they&#8217;re using.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And if you still have issues getting those sweet conversions, you can check out our post on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/5-reasons-why-your-website-is-not-converting/\">5 reasons your website traffic isn&#8217;t converting into customers</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let the best WordPress sitemap plugin do the heavy lifting for you!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">Click here to get started with AIOSEO today!</a></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/\">How to Create a Sitemap in WordPress (The Easy Way)</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://aioseo.com/how-to-create-a-sitemap-in-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:91:\"\n		\n		\n					\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n					\n			\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"100 SEO Statistics – Update Your Strategy for 2021\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=100-seo-statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 17 Dec 2020 13:00:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"SEO Tips\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"100 seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"ecommerce seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"local seo stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"search engine marketing statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"seo statistics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"video seo stats\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"https://aioseo.com/?p=22425\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:330:\"<p>Are you looking for up to date SEO statistics? We decided to compile a mega-list of 100 SEO statistics to help you update your SEO strategy for 2021.</p>\nThe post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/\">100 SEO Statistics – Update Your Strategy for 2021</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Stina Pettersson\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41738:\"<p>Are you looking for up to date SEO statistics?&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The world of search engine optimization (SEO) is complex and requires plenty of planning. <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Creating a website</a> or small business means you have to think carefully about your SEO strategy if you want to see your brand thrive. Understanding key SEO statistics will help you make smart and thoughtful marketing decisions in the future.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We decided to compile a mega-list of 100 SEO statistics with the goal of helping you get a better handle on your SEO so that you can get more email subscribers, sales, and traffic.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we look at the stats, we&#8217;re going to answer a very important question: </p>\n\n\n\n<p>“What is SEO?” </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once we define the term, we’ll go over stats across various industries and platforms to get a better understanding of SEO and its impact on your website.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s get started!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We want to help you navigate our compiled SEO statistics as quickly and efficiently as possible. Here’s a table of contents you can use to find the section that appeals to you.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"is-style-default\"><li><a href=\"#what-is-seo\">What is SEO?</a></li><li><a href=\"#google-ranking-factor-statistics\">Google Ranking Factor Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#local-seo-statistics\">Local SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#ecommerce-and-small-business-seo-statistics\">eCommerce and Small Business SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#video-seo-statistics\">Video SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#voice-search-seo-statistics\">Voice Search SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#mobile-seo-statistics\">Mobile SEO Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#search-engine-marketing-statistics\">Search Engine Marketing Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"#off-page-seo-statistics\">Off-Page SEO Statistics</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"what-is-seo\">What Is SEO?&nbsp;</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"397\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo.png\" alt=\"What is seo? All in One SEO (AIOSEO)\" class=\"wp-image-22426\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-300x169.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-704x396.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/what-is-seo-600x337.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>First, let&#8217;s explain what search engine optimization is, also known as SEO. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Essentially, SEO is the process of optimizing your site to rank high in search engines like Google so you can get more traffic to your site. The goal is to eventually make it to the first page of Google for your chosen keywords.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, but what do keywords really mean, you may think?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-do-keyword-research-for-your-wordpress-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Keywords </a>are ideas and topics that define what your site&#8217;s content is about. In terms of SEO, they&#8217;re the words and phrases that searchers enter into search engines, also called &#8220;search queries.&#8221; You want the keywords on your page to be relevant to what people are searching for so they have a better chance of finding your content among the results.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With that said, making it to the elusive first page of Google means that more people will find your website, which opens the door to some pretty exciting marketing opportunities.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can strengthen your SEO ranking in many ways. Some businesses focus heavily on optimizing their website and <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">fine-tuning their XML sitemap. </a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Others spend their time creating blog content and building a consistent traffic source from platforms like Facebook and YouTube, which correlates with improved search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, high-quality content and link building are two of the most important ranking factors according to <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/google-reveals-20-percent-queries-voice-queries-249917\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Land</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The truth is, you need to consider all of this if you want to make your website accessible to a broad audience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But that’s only the beginning.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>SEO is complex and can take some time to fully grasp, especially if you’re <a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/start-a-new-blog/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">new to blogging</a> or running a small business. The journey to the front page of Google requires you to think carefully and use SEO statistics to make your content and marketing decisions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now that we’ve defined SEO, let’s move on to the statistics.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"google-ranking-factor-statistics\">Google Ranking Factor Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can’t talk about SEO without bringing Google and ranking factors into the conversation. Google is the largest search engine in the world, and the most frequently visited website of all time. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see, the number of Google searches increase every year.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"490\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - Google searches per year\" class=\"wp-image-22427\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year-300x208.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/google-searches-per-year-600x416.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://www.internetlivestats.com/google-search-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Internet Live Stats</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Because of Google’s popularity, its ranking system for websites based on search relevance and performance is the standard used by virtually all business owners.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, Google uses over<a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ranking-factors#pagelevel\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 200 factors</a> in their algorithm for ranking websites. These <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/seo-ranking-factors/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">SEO ranking factors</a> include domain age, keywords, mobile-friendliness, number of internal links, and much more.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out some more interesting Google ranking factor stats:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Out of all of the website traffic in the world, <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/216573/worldwide-market-share-of-search-engines/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">86%</a> goes through Google&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li><a href=\"https://videos.brightedge.com/research-report/BrightEdge_ChannelReport2019_FINAL.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">68%</a> of online experiences start with a search engine</li><li>Believe it or not, Google receives <a href=\"https://www.internetlivestats.com/google-search-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3.5 billion</a> searches every single day</li><li>Research shows that <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/insiders/inbound-marketing-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">75%</a> of searchers don’t bother clicking past the results on the first page</li><li>The first 5 results for a given search account for <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/digital-marketing-statistics/#seostatistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">67%</a> of all clicks</li><li>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">91%</a> of all websites never receive organic traffic from Google due to not having backlinks</li><li><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/randfish/keepng-up-wth-seo-n-2017-beyond/11-Keyword_Length_of_Search_Queries1Word\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">54.31%</a> of search queries contain 3 or more words</li><li>The average person searches for something online <a href=\"https://ardorseo.com/blog/how-many-google-searches-per-day-2019/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">3-4 times</a> a day</li><li>Analysts predict that between <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/local-seo-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">16% and 20%</a> of all user searches are brand new keywords and phrases, which should get you excited about optimizing your content for new keywords</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>According to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a> pages with shorter URLs are often given favor in search rankings, as well as sites with a lower bounce rate and faster loading times.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Check your loading times with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/free-website-speed-test-tool-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">IsItWP’s FREE speed test</a> to see where you stand!</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-algorithm-history/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Journal</a> states that Google introduces thousands of changes to their search engine algorithm every year. With that said, if you want to win at SEO, you have to play by Google’s rules.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"local-seo-statistics\">Local SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>According to Google,<a href=\"https://www.socialmediatoday.com/news/12-local-seo-stats-every-business-owner-and-marketer-should-know-in-2019-i/549079/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 46%</a> of all Google searches are local. Local SEO is a little different from traditional SEO. Instead of targeting a global audience, it’s all about reaching people who live in a specific place.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business owners that have brick and mortar locations may take to the internet to promote their brand. Similarly, companies that offer a service like plumbing or electrical work use local SEO to reach their target audience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You’ll want to target keywords that use words that focus on location. If you have a sushi restaurant, you would want to use a keyword like “Sushi restaurants near me.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s also important that you list your business on Google so you can appear in the rankings. Include information about your company that new customers may need to know, such as your business hours, phone number, and address.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Including this information makes it easier for people to contact your company, which leads to more sales and visibility.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let’s continue with some interesting local SEO statistics.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"294\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - mobile searches statistics \" class=\"wp-image-22430\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-300x125.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-704x294.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-searches-statistics-600x250.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Think with Google</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The terms “Where to buy” and “near me” increased<a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"> 200%</a> over the past 2 years and search queries for “(store) near me” have grown <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">250% </a>over the same 2 years. You might be surprised to learn that 28% of local business searches eventually turn into a sale.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Around one-third of all searches mention specific locations and 97% of people learn about local companies online more than anywhere else.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not to forget the growing number of mobile users. Did you know that <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/advertising-channels/search/how-advertisers-can-extend-their-relevance-with-search-download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">18%</a> of smartphone users made a same-day purchase after performing a local search? When asked, 54% of mobile users said they look up hours of local businesses, while <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/advertising-channels/search/how-advertisers-can-extend-their-relevance-with-search-download/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">53% </a>looked up directions.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">56%</a> of local businesses that don’t have a listing on Google are losing out on potential customers. This statement is reinforced by the fact that 72% of people that use local search end up visiting a store within 5 miles.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4 out of 5 consumers say they want more personalized offers that relate to their location, and about 70% of people said that businesses should put call and direction buttons in their ads.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>More importantly, allowing reviews for your local business can increase visibility and result in <a href=\"https://trustpulse.com/online-review-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">73%</a> more consumers trusting your brand.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On a final note, long-tail keywords, such as those used when coming up with local keywords, generate <a href=\"https://moz.com/beginners-guide-to-seo/keyword-research\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">70%</a> more traffic when compared to commonly used shorter words. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want more details on how to optimize your website, please check out our <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">ultimate WordPress SEO guide.</a>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"ecommerce-and-small-business-seo-statistics\">eCommerce and Small Business SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We can’t have a list of SEO stats and not mention the importance of SEO for eCommerce and small business owners. Brands around the globe work on improving their SEO, so they can reach a broad audience that’s interested in their product or service.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business owners and marketing teams have a ton of cool tools they can to boost their SERP (Search Engine Result Pages) position.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The general theme is that you want to get as many businesses and consumers as possible to find out about your brand through social media, email, and by browsing Google.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s look at several small business and eCommerce SEO statistics you should keep in mind if you want to see your website make it to page 1 for your keywords.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"495\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - number of clicks on Google\" class=\"wp-image-22431\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics-300x210.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/number-of-clicks-google-statistics-600x421.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>An impressive <a href=\"https://retail.emarketer.com/article/more-product-searches-start-on-amazon/5b92c0e0ebd40005bc4dc7ae\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">35%</a> of all product searches begin with Google, and on average, <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/content-optimization\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">40%</a> of revenue comes from organic visitors. This is the free traffic that’s the most desirable for businesses, as well as for consumers it seems since&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.blogtyrant.com/new-blogging-statistics/#engagement-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">70-80% </a>tend to ignore paid content in favor of organic results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In fact, leads from search engines have a 14.6% conversion rate, which beats out outbound marketing practices like cold calling by over 700%. Actually, <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/content-optimization\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">51%</a> of traffic from B2B and B2C sites comes from search.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Did you know that businesses spend close to <a href=\"https://moz.com/rand/seo-consultant-agency-pricing-structure-services/#32\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$5,000</a> every month on their SEO strategy, and will spend <a href=\"https://www.borrellassociates.com/industry-papers/papers/trends-in-digital-marketing-services-april-16-detail\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$79.27 billion</a> on SEO by the end of the year?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On-page content, such as your blog, can increase traffic by as much as <a href=\"https://www.marketingsherpa.com/content_by_legacy_id?legacy_id=32133\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">2000%</a>, which can directly impact your SEO ranking. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Similarly, businesses that blog get <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">524%</a> more pages indexed by Google, and <a href=\"https://neilpatel.com/blog/38-content-marketing-stats-that-every-marketer-needs-to-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">72%</a> of business owners and marketers claim that content creation is their number tool for improving SEO.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Moving up 1 search engine results page (SERP) will boost your click-through rate by an average of <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/google-ctr-stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">30.8%</a>, which is fantastic. To be able to do this, it could be a good idea to pay extra attention to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko’s </a>research indicating that pages with at least one image, such as product pages, rank higher than businesses that only have descriptions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What is becoming more important for eCommerce businesses, is that the demand for same-day shipping is up <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/marketing-resources/omnichannel/meeting-shoppers-needs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">120% </a>compared to 2015, and that trend seems consistent in 2021. They better get their logistics on track so they can respond to this increased demand for same-day shipping.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, according to <a href=\"https://www.chatmeter.com/blog/growth-of-near-me-searches-shows-importance-of-local-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Chat Meter</a> responding to positive and negative feedback can help you improve your SEO ranking.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"video-seo-statistics\">Video SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing videos for SEO is now an extremely common practice. The surge of mobile devices and the ability to show YouTube results on Google make this a strategy you don’t want to miss out on in 2021.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can optimize your videos by including transcripts, creating a catchy title, and by using a thumbnail that matches the content, just to name a few things. Like other areas of SEO, all of these small tweaks can lead to significant results.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s explore some video SEO stats so we can learn more about this brand-building technique.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - does video give you a positive return on investment \" class=\"wp-image-22432\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-300x150.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-704x354.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/positive-return-on-investment-statistics-600x301.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To make you understand the incredible power of video content, we want to start by sharing that YouTube users watch <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/video-marketing-statistics-what-you-must-know/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1 billion</a> hours of content every day. And according to <a href=\"https://www.marketingcharts.com/digital/video-110520\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Marketing Charts</a>, it’s estimated that by 2021, the average person will watch 100 minutes of video content every day.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine that!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>YouTube is the second-largest search engine in the world, with over <a href=\"https://rafflepress.com/social-media-marketing-statistics/#YouTube-Social-Media-Marketing-Stats\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">1.9 billion</a> active monthly users, so this is a great source to tap into.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One of <a href=\"https://www.renderforest.com/blog/video-marketing-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Render Forest’s</a> surveys revealed that only 7 out of 10 marketers optimize their videos for search-ability, which is a bad judgment since <a href=\"https://chipthompson.com/19-fascinating-statistics-case-visual-content-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">85%</a> of consumers in the United States only watch video content. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Imagine the whole world!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Although, <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/state-of-video-marketing-new-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">92%</a> of marketers say they plan on adding videos to their marketing strategy. They should really consider this based on the fact that <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/state-of-video-marketing-new-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">88% </a>of marketers say that video delivers a positive return on investment.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, you’re 53% more likely to appear on the first page of Google if you add videos to your site, and you can also increase your organic SERP traffic by <a href=\"https://www.brightcove.com/en/blog/2015/08/create-compelling-video-experiences\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">157%</a>. That will surely lead to more conversions.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The truth is that landing pages with videos get <a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/AdelieStudios/adelie-studios-top16videomarketingstatistics2016-56658453\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">80%</a> more conversions. Including a video on your landing page also increases your chances of appearing on page 1 of Google by 53%.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, we’ve already mentioned the importance of blog content. Blog posts with videos have a stunning <a href=\"https://www.convinceandconvert.com/content-marketing/year-of-video-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">53x</a> greater chance of making it to the first page of Google, and adding videos to your blog posts can help you get <a href=\"https://moz.com/blog/what-makes-a-link-worthy-post-part-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3x</a> more inbound links.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"voice-search-seo-statistics\">Voice Search SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Voice search is quickly becoming one of the most popular ways consumers find out about brands around the world. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Optimizing your website for voice search means understanding what a consumer will likely say, instead of type. Strangely enough, these two things are often different, choosing the right keywords for voice optimization is crucial.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s now more convenient for people to simply talk into their phones or smart speakers instead of opening Google every time they have a question. Business owners and marketers realized that this trend was picking up early and got to work.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you haven’t started yet, don’t worry. It’s not too late to gear your site towards people using voice search.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>But before you get started, here are some helpful voice search SEO statistics.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"261\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-22434\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-300x111.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-704x261.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/voice-seo-statitics-1-600x222.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/think/docs/think-with-google-2019-research-review.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Think with Google</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The amazingly large number of 45 million people use voice assistants every single day, and Google Assistant usage has increased by <a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/data/google-assistant-user-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">400%</a> in the last year.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nationalpublicmedia.com/smart-audio-report/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Edison Research and NPR</a> mean that 1 in 6 Americans owns a smart speaker, making voice a common way to browse the internet, and&nbsp; 22% with smart speakers use their devices to buy products. This goes hand in hand with the fact that 40% of millennials use voice search to buy things online.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>What is more, <a href=\"https://www.pwc.com/us/en/services/consulting/library/consumer-intelligence-series/voice-assistants.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">61% </a>of people between the ages of 25 and 64 claim that they plan on using their smart speaker for searching more in the future, and by 2022, it’s predicted that <a href=\"https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/voice-shopping-set-to-jump-to-40-billion-by-2022-rising-from-2-billion-today-300605596.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">55%</a> of households will have a smart speaker.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Almost <a href=\"https://www.seoclarity.net/next-generation-search-voice-17099/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">20% </a>of all voice searches are triggered by 1 word in a set of 25. The three most common trigger words include how, what, and best. Furthermore, the average word count of a voice search result page is 2,312 words.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And for all shopping lovers, did you know that Amazon and Google are responsible for <a href=\"https://www.strategyanalytics.com/strategy-analytics/news/strategy-analytics-press-releases/2018/01/02/loyalty-or-lock-in-most-smart-speaker-users-won%27t-budge-from-amazon-or-google\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">94%</a> of smart speakers used by consumers?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You may also be surprised to learn that <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">40.7%</a> of voice search responses come directly from featured snippets.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned earlier, turning your blog posts into video content can improve your organic traffic on that post by <a href=\"https://www.searchenginepeople.com/blog/8-blogging-stats-2017-strategy.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">157%</a>. According to <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/youtube-ranking-factors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Backlinko</a> comments on your YouTube videos play a significant role in your ranking on search engines.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Mobile SEO ties into many of the topics we’ve talked about today. Specifically, video and voice search have hit such a high level of success due to smartphone and tablet users.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"mobile-seo-statistics\">Mobile SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"325\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - digital around the world stats\" class=\"wp-image-22436\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-300x138.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-704x325.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/mobile-seo-statistics-600x276.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When you’re optimizing your site or social media for SEO, you have to think carefully about the experience you’re providing for your mobile users. Sites that are not mobile-friendly can’t get ranked on Google, so mobile-readiness is a factor you need to consider.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t worry, we have your back. Here are plenty of mobile SEO statistics that will help you get started:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://wearesocial.com/blog/2020/04/digital-around-the-world-in-april-2020\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">5.16 billion</a> people have mobile devices, and over <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/277125/share-of-website-traffic-coming-from-mobile-devices/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">51%</a> of internet traffic comes from smartphones and tablets</li><li>Google drives <a href=\"https://www.hubspot.com/marketing-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">96%</a> of mobile traffic, and <a href=\"https://www.go-globe.hk/local-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">87%</a> of all mobile users interact with a search engine daily&nbsp;</li><li>The first organic search result for any given keyword gets <a href=\"https://www.seoclarity.net/mobile-desktop-ctr-study-11302/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">27.7%</a> of all clicks, and <a href=\"https://www.brightedge.com/resources/research-reports/mobile-first-57-traffic-now-mobile\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">79%</a> of all keywords show different Google results depending on whether a user is on desktop or mobile</li><li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/seo-statistics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">16.8 billion</a> smart speaker devices were shipped out by Amazon, Google, Apple, and other brands</li><li>Mobile voice searches are <a href=\"https://searchenginewatch.com/sew/opinion/2296905/how-will-voice-search-change-seo-for-local-stores-global-enterprises\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">3x</a> more likely to be based on a specific location</li><li><a href=\"https://www.thinkwithgoogle.com/marketing-resources/omnichannel/meeting-shoppers-needs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">60% </a>of smartphone users have bought a product that they discovered by using a search engine</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>We obviously like our smartphones. According to <a href=\"https://www.emarketer.com/content/mobile-time-spent-2018\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Emarketer</a>, most people spend 3 hours and 35 minutes on their smartphones every day.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, <a href=\"https://searchengineland.com/8-major-google-ranking-signals-2017-278450\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Search Engine Land</a> states that websites that aren’t mobile-friendly don’t rank on Google. Based on the fact that 61% of mobile users will contact a website if they discover a business website with a mobile-friendly layout it’s extremely important to ensure your site is mobile friendly.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"search-engine-marketing-statistics\">Search Engine Marketing Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Search engine marketing, also known as SEM, is an extremely popular marketing tactic that you can use for more growth. Simply put, SEM is a strategy where brands try to increase their visibility on search engines by using paid advertisements.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The goal is to get more people to click on your website, which will help you get more conversions and grow your lead list. We think that SEM is best used when combined with other areas of SEO, and experts agree.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data from SEM campaigns can help you learn more about your target audience, which in turn opens the door for more optimization opportunities.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - top 4 reasons people click on paid search ads\" class=\"wp-image-22438\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics-300x174.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/paid-search-ads-statistics-600x348.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s show you some stats that confirm this statement. For starters, the average company sees a <a href=\"https://www.powertraffick.com/google-ads-statistics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">200%</a> ROI with Google Ads, and <a href=\"https://databox.com/seo-vs-ppc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">86%</a> of experts use PPC (Pay Per Click) data to improve their SEO strategy. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is a smart move because stats show that if a consumer clicks a PPC advertisement, they are <a href=\"https://www.wordlead.com/facts/ppc-statistics-adwords-trends/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">50% </a>more likely to buy a product when compared to organic traffic. They have higher shopping intent.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a matter of fact, one survey revealed that <a href=\"https://clutch.co/seo-firms/resources/search-engine-marketing-why-people-click-paid-search-ads\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">75%</a> of participants found paid search ads made finding what they were looking for easier, and 26% of people clicked on paid advertisements because they were familiar with the brand. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, 33% of respondents said they click on paid search ads because the promotional post answers their query.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not really surprising considering Google is the search giant, and in 2019, Google made over <a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/266249/advertising-revenue-of-google/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$134 billion</a> in profits from prioritized search ads. However, the spending on text ads went down <a href=\"https://www.merkleinc.com/thought-leadership/digital-marketing-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">14%</a>, but shopping on Google increased by 41% between 2018 and 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Google is probably not crying crocodile tears since its advertising and search tools helped the company bring a staggering <a href=\"https://comparecamp.com/sem-statistics/#TOC3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">$330 billion</a> to the U.S. market in 2018.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"off-page-seo-statistics\">Off-Page SEO Statistics</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Off-page SEO is one of the most important aspects of growing your business. If other brands and websites aren’t linking to your company, and people aren’t sharing your posts on social media, you’re going to have a hard time ranking on Google.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Luckily, there are plenty of ways for you to improve your off-page SEO. We want to help you unravel the mystery once and for all by looking at some compelling off-page SEO stats.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"706\" height=\"376\" src=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics.png\" alt=\"100 SEO Statistics - referring domain stats\" class=\"wp-image-22439\" srcset=\"https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics.png 706w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-300x160.png 300w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-704x376.png 704w, https://aioseo.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/referring-domain-statistics-600x320.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 706px) 100vw, 706px\" /><figcaption>Image Source: <a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">Ahrefs</a></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To start with, there’s a strong correlation between <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/social-media-and-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">social media popularity and SEO ranking</a> on Google. This is due to the fact that social media content is extremely shareable, so your site will get more traffic and visibility.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For instance, articles shared on social media see a <a href=\"https://blog.hootsuite.com/social-media-seo-experiment/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">22%</a> performance increase compared to those not shared. Google even crawls social media for relevant information. It’s no surprise that <a href=\"https://databox.com/social-media-and-seo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">91%</a> of marketers spend time optimizing their profiles for maximum exposure.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Better yet, websites with blogs tend to get <a href=\"https://www.stateofinbound.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">97%</a> more backlinks, which is one of the most important factors for SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Generally, the top result on page one for a popular keyword has nearly <a href=\"https://backlinko.com/search-engine-ranking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">35,000 </a>backlinks. To build backlinks may seem like a walk in the park, but it’s not. In fact, <a href=\"https://www.smartinsights.com/digital-marketing-strategy/100-must-see-marketing-stats/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">65%</a> of marketers say that building backlinks is the most challenging aspect of SEO.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And you soon realize the difficulty in building backlinks when&nbsp;<a href=\"https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">66.31%</a> of pages don’t have a single backlink, as well as half of businesses use <a href=\"https://comparecamp.com/sem-statistics/#TOC3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">25%</a> of their budget to build links. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Other companies spend an average of $1000 per month on their link building strategy. It adds up!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ahrefs stats show that the number 1 position for a given keyword gets 5-14% more backlinks from new business websites, and better yet, infographics generate <a href=\"https://www.quicksprout.com/content-marketing-lessons-learned/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\">37.5%</a> more backlinks than traditional content.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>On a final note, other tactics for <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/get-more-backlinks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">improving off-site SEO</a> include guest posting and giving testimonials to other businesses.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There you have it!&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve now looked at over 100 SEO statistics that you can use to grow your business. You’re not going to see your business climb through the ranks overnight, but making it to page 1 of Google is entirely possible.&nbsp; </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/ultimate-wordpress-seo-guide/\">SEO </a>is a lot like life, the more you put in, the more you’ll get out of it. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you want to see your site beat the competitors and get tons of organic traffic, you have to put in the effort to optimize your brand for search optimization across all platforms.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Thankfully, <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/\">All in One SEO (AIOSEO)</a> makes the SEO process easy!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>AIOSEO is the best WordPress SEO plugin, and it offers all the tools you&#8217;ll need to easily and efficiently optimize your site and improve search engine rankings.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not using it yet? What are you waiting for?</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://aioseo.com/pricing/\">Click here to get started with AIOSEO today!</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>The post <a href=\"https://aioseo.com/100-seo-statistics/\">100 SEO Statistics – Update Your Strategy for 2021</a> first appeared on <a href=\"https://aioseo.com\">AIOSEO</a>.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wel